  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Prompt Injection as Role Confusion",
      "url": "https://role-confusion.github.io",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/vwin4l",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "LolPython",
      "published": "2026-06-22T17:22:07Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLM prompt injection stems from failing to separate control and data planes, leading models to confuse system roles with untrusted user inputs.",
        "Mitigate role confusion by utilizing structural APIs like ChatML or deploying dual-model architectures to strictly isolate system and user instruction contexts.",
        "Engineers must evaluate LLM robustness using automated red-teaming frameworks that specifically target system-prompt versus user-input boundary degradation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Rhombus v1.0: A Racket flavored language with syntax",
      "url": "https://blog.racket-lang.org/2026/06/rhombus-v1.0.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/bkwkz5",
      "score": 13,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "orib",
      "published": "2026-06-22T17:54:04Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Rhombus v1.0 delivers a modern, conventional syntax similar to Python, built on top of the Racket ecosystem.",
        "It preserves Racket's powerful macro system and language-oriented programming without requiring traditional Lisp S-expression parentheses.",
        "The release enables building custom domain-specific languages utilizing an extensible, indentation-sensitive, and operator-precedence-based parser."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Mark-of-the-web and pinning installers to sites",
      "url": "https://blog.randomoracle.io/2026/06/20/mark-of-the-web-and-pinning-installers-to-sites/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/z4vrld",
      "score": 9,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "raymii",
      "published": "2026-06-21T05:35:25Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Mark-of-the-Web (MOTW) utilizes NTFS Alternate Data Streams (Zone.Identifier) to trigger SmartScreen warnings on downloaded files.",
        "Threat actors bypass MOTW using container formats like ISOs and ZIPs, necessitating additional verification layers for installers.",
        "Pinning installers to authorized download domains mitigates malvertising by ensuring payloads only execute when fetched from trusted origins."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I am dreading our LLM-written incident report future",
      "url": "https://surfingcomplexity.blog/2026/06/19/i-am-dreading-our-llm-written-incident-report-future/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ysxvko",
      "score": 43,
      "comments": 16,
      "author": "azhenley",
      "published": "2026-06-20T00:51:33Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLM-generated post-mortems risk smoothing over human errors, replacing deep blameless analysis with generic, plausible-sounding boilerplate.",
        "Automated reports satisfy compliance and management checklists but fail to provide SREs with actionable technical lessons to prevent future outages.",
        "Offloading documentation to GenAI tools degrades the critical DevOps practice of post-incident reflection and team-wide collaborative learning."
      ]
    },
